Using such an enhanced trigger system consolidates ease of use and safety into a convenient, innovative trigger operation—one that reduces the chance of unintended firing. title: For Sale:  Winchester 1911SL Semi Auto 12ga Shotgun "The Widowmaker"
postcontent:
Trades welcome!

What I have for sale is a very rare piece of history, a Winchester model 1911 SL 12 gauge semi auto shotgun. It was manufactured in 1913 and all serial nubers match. It was winchester's first attempt at a semi auto shotgun and trying to work around John M. Browning's patents of the time!!! It cocks from the barrel instead of a charging handle. It was dubbed "the widdow maker" due to a series of accidents caused by poor gun handling techniques.

This firearm has a 5 round capacity and features a 26" full choke barrel. All original blueing(very worn) and all original parts. This gun was used a lot by my great grandfather and shows the wear. It still functions properly.

Text OR email if interested.

title: For Sale:  Finnish capture M91/30 with RARE factory blued bolt
postcontent:
Up for SALE is the last of the mosins I own...a 1938 Tula M91/30 that is all matching (with original parts not the scrubbed and restamped Mosins you see today) with the correct stock.  The Finnish did cut the stock in half and resplice it's front end with a Finnish type of wood, giving it a neat finger jointed look to the bottom of the stock.  They then refinished it which gives it a nice dark color. 

It came from the factory with a blued bolt, some people suspect the Finnish did it during re arsenal.  It's possible, I have seen only one other 1938 with a blued bolt on a popular forum that was not a Finnish capture.  Maybe they did it for a small run of rifles?  There was probably a few more of them but they were lost to WW2 or had the blued bolts replaced with freshly sanitized and restamped bolts.

The original bluing on this rifle is pretty nice.  I suppose it was only dropped once then picked up.  Lots of Finnish capture 91/30's ended up in Finnish artillery units so that could explain it's rather nice condition.  Bore is excellent.  because of that.  Sharp, crisp rifling with no pitting.  Shiny.  The Finns also sighted it in without the huge bayonet on.  If you don't have bad marksmanship you can reach out to some impressive distances, as far as your eyesight allows accuracy.  :)  I can repeatedly hit a man size brightly colored gong at a little over 300m with this no problem!

No trades at all.  Due to the recent acquisition of some new toys I am out of space in the safe so I must part with it.  (F0ur79)4threef0ur-zero.0.nine.9
